"Abstract Computer security is a discipline which comprises two very separate elements. On the one side the computer specialists are trained to improve the efficiency of the organisation, whilst on the other the security specialists are required to contain the risks against the organisation. At first sight there seems little to draw these groups together. Their training, attitudes and methods differ fundamentally, yet it is essential, if effective computer security is ever to be achieved, that they work in harmony towards the common goal. But for too long computer staff have been left to their own devices, and for too long security staff have buried their heads in the sand. Martin Smith examines the problem in the first of a series of articles on the “people factor” in computer security."
